### Environment information

* `brownie` Version: 1.17.0
* `ganache-cli` Version: any
* `solc` Version: any
* Python Version: any
* OS: osx/linux/win

### What was wrong?

`Contract.get_verification_info()` does not traverse dependency packages, it only returns main source file.

As I investigated further I found out that regex that is used for detect import pattern use double quote ( \" ) to separate path but my code use single quote, e.g. `import './xxx/yyy.sol'` instead of `import "./xxx/yyy.sol"`, because of a formatter.

Could it be possible to support both double quote and single quote regex for checking package?

Another example that use single quote:
https://github.com/Uniswap/v2-periphery/blob/master/contracts/UniswapV2Router02.sol

example:
A.sol
```// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity 0.8.7;

import './B.sol';

contract A is B {
  uint public x;

  constructor() B() {}

  function setX(uint _x) external {
    require(msg.sender == owner, '!owner');
    x = _x;
  }
}
```

B.sol
```
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity 0.8.7;

contract B {
  address public owner;

  constructor() {
    owner = msg.sender;
  }

  function setOwner(address _owner) public virtual {
    owner = _owner;
  }
}
```

### How can it be fixed?

change regex format from
`IMPORT_PATTERN = re.compile(r"(?<=\n)?import(?P<prefix>.*)\"(?P<path>.*)\"(?P<suffix>.*)(?=\n)")`
to
`IMPORT_PATTERN = re.compile(r"(?<=\n)?import(?P<prefix>.*)(\'|\")(?P<path>.*)(\'|\")(?P<suffix>.*)(?=\n)")`
